03/06/2004
THESSALONIKI, Greece -- Defence Minister Spilios Spiliotopoulos visited NATO multinational headquarters at the 3rd Army Corps facilities in Thessaloniki on Wednesday (2 June). Spiliotopoulos was briefed about the progress in developing the headquarters, expected to launch full operation with a staff of 200-250 officers within a year. At present, 105 officers work at the headquarters, most of them Greek. (MPA - 02/06/04)
